Tesseract-OCR/
# Ignore the user-data asset subdirs (photos, previews, thumbnails, uploaded
# documents), but keep top-level asset CODE tracked (custom.css, camera.js).
# NB: a blanket `assets/` can't be undone by `!assets/*.css` — git won't
# re-include a file whose parent dir is excluded — so target the subdirs.
assets/images/
assets/thumbnails/
assets/previews/
assets/documents/
logs/
*.csv
*.json
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
*.log
